<h3 id="head-4337ef337ecbae01528ec15aa4029353fd42657c"><a href="#bottom"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-bottom.png" alt="[BOTTOM]" height="10" width="14"></a><a href="#top"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-top.png" alt="[TOP]" height="10" width="14"></a>Skeleton</h3>
<p>
As undead beings,<a class="interwiki" title="Self" href="./Skeleton"><img src="./wiki/starshine/img/moin-inter.png" alt="[Self]" height="16" width="16">skeleton</a>s need to worry very little about poison or  attacks that can drain life. They do not really use eyes for perceiving  things, and are thus not fooled by invisibility. Their bones are resistant to sharp shrapnels (not much to cut there), and they will quickly become resistant to cold. 
</p>
<p>
It is very hard for skeletons to eat food or drink potions. Although the magical effects of these will affect the skeleton even without entering the  skeleton's (non-existent) belly, the potion / food itself will fall  through the skeleton's jaws, giving no nutritional benefit. 
</p>

